    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to examples of the knitting machine invented by William Lee of Cambridge, England in 1589. It produced net composed of the basic looped ‘stocking stitch’ and thus superseded hand-knitting. The introduction of this technology initiated the process of mechanizing the textile industry.</Note_Text>
